Applications choose a transport protocol based on their specific needs for reliability or speed.
Protocol
Function
Transport Layer
HTTP
Web page access/request-response
TCP (Reliable)
DNS
Translates names (www.iitkgp.ac.in) to IP addresses
UDP (Fast)
FTP
Large-scale, reliable file transfers
TCP (Reliable)
TFTP
Trivial FTP; small, easy to implement for router images
UDP (Connectionless)
SMTP
Sending and receiving electronic mail
TCP (Reliable)
SNMP
Exchange of network management information
UDP (Best-effort)
Telnet
Remote login to execute commands via command line
TCP (Reliable)
